These instructions will get server.js working on your computer.

Install node.js here with the default settings:
https://nodejs.org/en/download/

Run npm --h to ensure that npm has been installed correctly.

Run these commands in terminal to install the necessary packages:
npm install express --save
npm install ejs --save
npm install cookie-parser --save

Finally, run:
node server.js

The server should be on port 8080.
